quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  6,145,"Say, \"I cannot find, in what I am inspired with, anything unlawful for the eater to eat thereof, except it be carrion, or shed blood, or the flesh of swine - for that is foul - or an abomination that is consecrated to other than Allah. But he who is"
  6,146,"To those who were Jews did We prohibit everything that hath a solid (undivided) hoof; and of oxen and sheep did We prohibit to them the fat, save what the backs of both do bear, or their entrails, or what is mixed with bone; this in recompense for their r"
  6,147,"And if they give you the lie, say, \"your Lord is of all-embracing Mercy, but His Wrath shall never be withdrawn from the guilty"
  6,148,"Those who associate partners with Allah will say, \"Had Allah pleased, we would not associated partners (with Him), nor our fathers; nor should we have forbidden aught.\" Thus did they give the lie to those who came before them, until they tasted"
  6,149,"Say, \"Allah´s is the final (searching, conclusive, decisive) argument; and had He pleased He would have guided you all"
  6,150,"Say, \"Bring forward your witnesses to prove that Allah has forbidden these!\" But if they do bring such witnesses, bear you not witness with them; nor follow the vain desires of those who say Our Signs (revelations) are lies, and those who believ"